Introduction

Xu Jia Qi (simplified chinese: 许佳琪) is a Chinese idol singer under Star48 Culture Media. She is a graduated member of the Chinese idol group SNH48 (Team SII) and active member of its sub-unit 7SENSES.
She is a former member of the Chinese project girl group THE9 before their disbandment in 2021.

Team History:
[2012.10.14] - Joined SNH48 as a Research Student.
[2013.04.17] - Promoted to Team Unknown.
[2013.11.11] - Transferred to Team SII (Team SII Formation)
[2017.04.07] - Joined 7SENSES (SEN7ES Formation)
[2020.05.30] - Finished at 3rd place on Youth With You 2020, joining THE9.
[2020.05.30] - Hiatus from SNH48 Team SII and 7SENSES due to participating in THE9.
[2020.10.14] - Graduated from SNH48 Team SII (Announcement: July 27, 2019 | Graduation Stage: October 3, 2020)
[2021.12.06] - THE9 disbandment.
[2021.12.06] - Return to SNH48 7SENSES.
[2021.12.28] - Debuted as Star48 soloist.
